						<div class="postbody">Speaking as a non-developer, I don't know much about the math. I would like to clarify that "3D-type" parallax scrolling on the NES uses timed code to decide the scroll position(?) for each scanline; a mapper-based IRQ (if present) is used only to define the start or end of the effect. (I'm just trying to explain why the thread's title is inaccurate; feel free to correct me on this oversimplification.)</div>

					
